on  johnson since  she previously held leadership positions at bayer medical care medco health solutions nabisco and whirlpool corporation contents  early life and education  business career  johnson  johnson  honors and awards  references early life and educationedit the youngest of six children peterson received her bachelors degree in government studies from cornell university and her mpa in applied economics from princeton university she began her career working in consulting at mckinsey  company business careeredit from  to  peterson worked in strategy finance sustainability and product development at whirlpool corporation and later at nabisco in  peterson accepted a leadership position at medco health solutions in  she became president of bayer medical care she also received a fellowship from the robert bosch foundation in stuttgart germany and spent a year serving with the german federal ministry of finance and the federation of german industries in  she was promoted to chairman and chief executive officer of bayer cropscience ag peterson was formerly the chair of the conservation research charity ecohealth alliance previously called wildlife trust since  peterson has served on the board of directors at dun  bradstreet and owns more than  shares of the company in  she joined the board of directors of microsoft peterson often advocates for women in business and was featured in a multipart series of interviews on the subject by forbes in  she is a trustee of the institute for advanced study in princeton new jersey johnson  johnsonedit in december  peterson accepted a position at johnson  johnson as group worldwide chairman which made her the highestranking woman at the company the wall street journal reported that johnson  johnson had wooed peterson during the hiring process for several months before peterson was hired the company had been reported as having difficulties with product recalls and declining sales petersons hiring was part of a companywide overhaul meant to address these issues peterson also joined the companys executive committee and relocated from germany where she had worked for bayer to new brunswick new jersey where johnson  johnson is headquartered at johnson  johnson peterson was vocal about the companys need to further the roles of women in the workplace by  the company had doubled its number of women in executive leadership positions to  of its corporate staff when interviewed about the change peterson said if you think of it the population is half female so thats where we should be in terms of leadership we feel pretty good but we still have a long way to go honors and awardsedit in  the national association for female executives gave peterson their woman of achievement award in  peterson received the corporate vision award from gildas club new york city a charity foundation supporting cancer victims and their families  that same year forbes ranked peterson at number  on its list of the most powerful women in business in  the committee of  named peterson the recipient of its annual corporate innovator award in june  peterson traveled to berlin to give a presentation on healthcare policy to government leaders at the g summit as of september  bloomberg businessweek estimates petersons annual salary to be more than  million referencesedit  a b c d e f g sandra e peterson to join johnson  johnson as group worldwide chairman and member of the executive committee pharma business week  september   accessdate requires url help  a b c d executive profilesandra e peterson bloomberg businessweek retrieved  september    wildlife trust board of directors announce new leadership ecohealth alliance retrieved  september    new officers elected by ecohealth alliance board of directors committee chairs selected ecohealth alliance retrieved  september    dun  bradstreet board of directors dun  bradstreet retrieved  september    sasha galbraith  december  bayer cropsciences sandra peterson successful woman ceo navigat